# PowerShell Deploy Command

After making any code changes to this project, **always** include a ready-to-run PowerShell command for the user to commit and deploy (e.g. to Vercel).

## Format

```powershell
cd c:\Users\stytu\pyth-tracker; git add .; git commit -m "Short description"; git push
```

## Customization

- Change the commit message to describe the actual changes
- Use `;` (semicolon) between commands for PowerShell compatibility
- Do not use `&&` — it does not work in PowerShell
